description: From Latin transumere, transumptum (“to take from one to another”), in Latin [Term?] (“to transcribe”). See transume.

entries.meaning: (obsolete) A copy or exemplification of a record.
examples: Edward Lee the Kings Almoner; who, sending the transumpt of the Breve to the King April 23, by a Letter 12 of June following, also certified our King of the sending of Gonçales Fernando […]
